DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Eosinophil Outcome Percentage Integer::1 Decimal Place Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The 1 decimal place numeric laboratory value measured, assigned or computed related to the assessment of the percentage of eosinophils in a specimen.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the results of a medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for eosinophils, granular leukocytes with a nucleus that usually has two lobes connected by a slender thread of chromatin and cytoplasm containing coarse, round granules that are uniform in size and stainable by eosin.
